{
  "doc_id": "43622",
  "text": "By Slutsky's Lemma, all we need to prove is that AV AR → P AV AR. Given the form of AV AR, this can be shown using exactly the same line of reasoning as for the general theorem replacing g by h in all our estimates and combining the results with Corollary 3.7 in [CITATION_1] in lieu of Theorem 3.2, except that there is no scaling by n 1/2 in front of the estimates and no bias term. Since the C 3 property of g is only used once when handling the bias term in Lemma 6.6, the fact that h is only of class C 2 is not problematic.",
