      "span_text": "By Slutsky's Lemma, all we need to prove is that AV AR → P AV AR. Given the form of AV AR, this can be shown using exactly the same line of reasoning as for the general theorem replacing g by h in all our estimates and combining the results with Corollary 3.7 in  in lieu of Theorem 3.2, except that there is no scaling by n 1/2 in front of the estimates and no bias term.",
